data types 
         * List
            - collection of values or an items of different types.
             eg:  l1=["ABHI",34,"RAM"]
                  l2=[1,2,3,4,5,6]
           -  negative Indexing
           -  updating list values
                 list=[1,2,3,4,5,6]
                 list[2]=10
                 list=[1,2,10,4,5,6]
                 list[1:3]=[89,78]
                 list=[1,89,78,4,5,6]
                 list.append(10)
                 del list[2]
                 list.remove(4)

           -operations
              *Repatition operation
                  eg:L1=[1,2,3] ,L2=[4,5,6]
                     L2*2=[1,2,3,1,2,3]
              *concatenation
                  eg: L1+L2=[1,2,3,4,5,6]
              *Membership
              *Iteration
              *length
                  eg:len(L1)=3
         
             ### list built in function
               * cmp(list1,list2)  - compares the element of both the list (0 if true ,-1 is false)
               *len(list)
               *max(list)
               *min(list)
               *list(seg)


